    "Challenge 8 How to pre-train and apply LLM while ensuring data privacy?User data in a database must be protected from leakage due to privacy concerns.",
    "This prevents user data from being integrated into the database provider for centralized LLM pre-training.",
    "Moreover, some users cannot send their sensitive data as input to DB-GPT through inference APIs.Vision 8 To address this challenge, we propose two solutions.",
    "First, we can use privacy-preserving federated learning to train LLM [30,31].",
    "In this approach, a server (e.g., database provider) collaborates with clients (e.g., users) to train LLM for several rounds."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "First, we can use privacy-preserving federated learning to train LLM [30,31]."
  ]
